@grafik1, you are wrong, R5 is just a DVD with audio other than english released to different regions before the official release of english DVD to fight piracy.

What the guys do is take the R5 release and re-encode it with an english audio taken from another source normally CAM (as the english DVD is not released as yet).

And thats why the Video looks good and audio is not but sometimes if the cam is good enough, then the audio will be good as well.

